# 🔍 Search & Research

Tools focused on finding high-quality, relevant information.

- **Exa MCP** → Semantic web search (great for deep research and non-obvious sources)
- **Tavily MCP** → Fast, real-time search + summarized answers (more “Google-like” but AI-optimized)
- **Context7 MCP** → Structured docs + version-aware references (best for dev documentation)
- **Ref MCP** → Internal knowledge retrieval (think company docs, specs, private data)

👉 **Typical combo:**  
Exa + Tavily + Context7 = very strong “AI researcher” stack

---

# 🌐 Web Scraping & Data Extraction

Tools that pull structured data from websites.

- **Firecrawl MCP** → Clean scraping + multi-page crawling
- **Chrome DevTools MCP** → Live browser inspection + manual/interactive scraping

👉 **Difference:**

- Firecrawl = automated pipelines
- Chrome DevTools = debugging + dynamic/manual extraction

👉 **Typical combo:**  
Firecrawl + Chrome DevTools = robust scraping + debugging setup

---

# 🤖 Browser Automation & Testing

Tools that simulate real user behavior.

- **Playwright MCP** → Full browser automation (tests, flows, scraping with interaction)

👉 **Typical combo:**  
Playwright + Firecrawl = scraping + interaction (login, clicks, pagination)

---

# 💻 Development & Code Management

Tools that interact with codebases and engineering workflows.

- **GitHub MCP** → Repo access, PRs, issues on GitHub
- **Linear MCP** → Issue tracking + project management via Linear

👉 **Typical combo:**  
GitHub + Linear = full engineering loop (code + tasks)

---

# 🧠 Knowledge Management & Notes

Tools for organizing and retrieving structured knowledge.

- **Obsidian MCP** → Works with Obsidian vaults for personal/team knowledge bases
- **Ref MCP** (also fits here) → Internal documentation retrieval

👉 **Typical combo:**  
Obsidian + Ref = “second brain” for agents

---

# 🎨 UI / App Generation

Tools that help build interfaces or generate code visually.

- **Magic MCP** → AI-driven UI/component/code generation (design → code workflows)

👉 Often paired with GitHub for shipping generated code.
